              "level": 2,
              "heading": "Evaluation After Arriving at the",
              "page": 4,
              "content": "",
              "refs": []
            },
            {
              "id": "g003_s23_05",
              "level": 2,
              "heading": "Hospital",
              "page": 4,
              "content": "Recommendations",
              "refs": []
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "g003_s24",
          "level": 1,
          "heading": "1. The clinical use of a stroke severity scoring scale",
          "page": 4,
          "content": "is recommended, and NIHSS is preferred. (COR I, LOE B-NR)",
          "refs": [],
          "subsections": []
        },
        {
          "id": "g003_s25",
          "level": 1,
          "heading": "2. All patients with suspected AIS shall receive emer-",
          "page": 4,
          "content": "gency brain imaging evaluation. (COR I, LOE A)",
          "refs": [],
          "subsections": []
        },
        {
          "id": "g003_s26",
          "level": 1,
          "heading": "3. Before the patient receives IVT, non-contrast com-",
          "page": 4,
          "content": "puted tomography (CT) scan of the brain is effec- tive to rule out intracranial hemorrhage. (COR I, LOE A)",
          "refs": [],
          "subsections": [
            {
              "id": "g003_s26_01",
              "level": 2,
              "heading": "Imaging Evaluation for Indications of",
              "page": 4,
              "content": "",
              "refs": []
            },
            {
              "id": "g003_s26_02",
              "level": 2,
              "heading": "IVT",
              "page": 4,
              "content": "Recommendations",
              "refs": []
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "g003_s27",
          "level": 1,
          "heading": "1. Since the efficacy of IVT is related to the start time",
          "page": 4,
          "content": "of treatment, treatment shall be started as soon as possible for patients with indications and shall not be delayed by performing additional multimodal neuroimaging, such as CT perfusion and magnetic resonance perfusion. (COR I, LOE B-NR)",
          "refs": [],
          "subsections": []
        },
        {
          "id": "g003_s28",
          "level": 1,
          "heading": "2. For patients with AIS whose stroke symptoms are",
          "page": 4,
          "content": "first noted upon awakening from sleep or have an unknown time of stroke onset but exceeding",
          "refs": [],
          "subsections": []
        },
        {
          "id": "g003_s29",
          "level": 1,
          "heading": "4.5 hours from the last time known to be normal,",
          "page": 4,
          "content": "finding an imaging mismatch between diffu- sion-weighted imaging and fluid-attenuated inver- sion recovery of magnetic resonance imaging in the region of brain ischemia is helpful for IVT. 14 (COR IIa, LOE B-R)",
          "refs": [],
          "subsections": []
        },
        {
          "id": "g003_s30",
          "level": 1,
          "heading": "3. For patients with AIS whose symptoms occurred",
          "page": 4,
          "content": "between 4.5 and 9.0 hours after stroke onset or those on awakening with stroke (if within 9 hours from the midpoint of sleep), using CT perfusion to identify patients who had hypoperfused but salvageable brain tissue is helpful for patients to receive IVT. 15 (COR IIa, LOE B-R)",
          "refs": [],
          "subsections": [
            {
              "id": "g003_s30_01",
              "level": 2,
              "heading": "Imaging Evaluation for Indications of",
              "page": 4,
              "content": "",
              "refs": []
            },
            {
              "id": "g003_s30_02",
              "level": 2,
              "heading": "EVT",
              "page": 4,
              "content": "Recommendations",
              "refs": []
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "g003_s31",
          "level": 1,
          "heading": "1. For patients who are eligible for EVT, noninvasive",
          "page": 4,
          "content": "intracranial arterial angiography, such as CT angi- ography or magnetic resonance angiography, shall be performed as the initial imaging evaluation. (COR I, LOE A)",
          "refs": [],
          "subsections": []
        },
        {
          "id": "g003_s32",
          "level": 1,
          "heading": "2. For patients who are suspected LVO and eligible",
          "page": 4,
          "content": "for EVT and without a history of renal function impairment, it is reasonable to perform CT angiog- raphy before obtaining the serum creatinine result. (COR IIa, LOE B-NR)",
          "refs": [],
          "subsections": []
        },
        {
          "id": "g003_s33",
          "level": 1,
          "heading": "3. For patients who are potentially indicated for EVT,",
          "page": 4,
          "content": "in addition to intracranial vascular examinations, it is reasonable to perform extracranial carotid and cervical vertebral angiography, which can provide useful information on whether the patients are suit- able for treatment and endovascular treatment plan. (COR IIa, LOE C-EO)",
          "refs": [],
          "subsections": []
        },
        {
          "id": "g003_s34",
          "level": 1,
          "heading": "4. It may be reasonable to consider the condition of",
          "page": 4,
          "content": "collateral circulation to determine whether cer- tain patients are suitable for EVT. (COR IIb, LOE C-LO)",
          "refs": [],
          "subsections": []
        },
        {
          "id": "g003_s35",
          "level": 1,
          "heading": "5. For patients with LVO in the anterior circulation",
          "page": 4,
          "content": "presenting 6–24 hours from the last time known to Hsieh et al. 16Journal of Acute Medicine 11(1) 2021 be normal, it is recommended to use CT perfusion imaging or magnetic resonance diffusion-weighted imaging and/or perfusion imaging in assisting the selection of patients suitable for EVT. However, this recommendation is made only if the patients meet the eligibility criteria of either DAWN or DE- FUSE 3 trial. 16,17 (COR I, LOE A)",
          "refs": [],
          "subsections": [
            {
              "id": "g003_s35_01",
              "level": 2,
              "heading": "Other Diagnostics",
              "page": 5,
              "content": "Recommendations",
              "refs": []
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "g003_s36",
          "level": 1,
          "heading": "1. For all patients, blood glucose testing must be per-",
          "page": 5,
          "content": "formed before starting IVT. (COR I, LOE B-NR)",
          "refs": [],
          "subsections": []
        },
        {
          "id": "g003_s37",
          "level": 1,
          "heading": "2. A baseline electrocardiogram is recommended for",
          "page": 5,
          "content": "patients with AIS, but it shall not delay the start of IVT. (COR I, LOE B-NR)",
          "refs": [],
          "subsections": []
        },
        {
          "id": "g003_s38",
          "level": 1,
          "heading": "3. A baseline troponin test is recommended for pa-",
          "page": 5,
          "content": "tients with AIS, but it shall not delay the start of IVT or EVT. (COR I, LOE C-LD)",
          "refs": [],
          "subsections": []
        },
        {
          "id": "g003_s39",
          "level": 1,
          "heading": "4. In the absence of evidence of acute lung, heart, and",
          "page": 5,
          "content": "pulmonary vascular disease, it is uncertain wheth- er a chest X-ray image is useful in the hyperacute phase of the stroke. If this test is performed, it shall not delay the start of IVT. (COR IIb, LOE B-NR)",
          "refs": [],
          "subsections": [
            {
              "id": "g003_s39_01",
              "level": 2,
              "heading": "Conflicts of Interest Statement",
              "page": 5,
              "content": "None.",
              "refs": []
            },
            {
