        {
          "id": "g004_s259",
          "level": 1,
          "heading": "ABSTRACT",
          "page": 30,
          "content": "In the past 7 years, several important antiplatelet trials have been completed with pivotal findings. These results were significant and have been already changing the daily practice of treatment for ischemic stroke (IS). One of the most important findings is the concept of dual antiplatelet therapy for acute noncardioembolic IS or transient ischemic attack. The timing and duration of antiplatelet therapy also have significant impact on the outcomes of IS. In addition to traditional antiplatelet…",
