          "heading": "ABSTRACT",
          "page": 28,
          "content": "Stroke is one of the most important causes of epilepsy. With the advancement of medicine, the mortality rate of stroke keeps decline, then the stroke survivors have become a high-risk group of epilepsy due to damage to the brain cells. The first edition of the \"Guideline for Post-Stroke Epilepsy Management\" co-edited by Taiwan Epilepsy Society and Taiwan Stroke Society in 2015. During the past six years, many anti-epileptic drugs with new mechanisms have been launched. After the consensus of Tai…",
