          "page": 2,
          "content": "Hypertension is the most important risk factor for stroke. In recent years, guidelines for the treatment of hypertension world- wide have been continually updated (Table 1). With accumu- lating clinical evidence, diagnostic criteria of hypertension have changed from emphasizing the importance of diastolic BP in the 1980s to the importance of systolic BP in the 1990s, especially since the Joint National Committee 7 published guidelines for the treatment of hypertension in 2003. Controlling patien…",
