          "id": "g024_s107",
          "level": 1,
          "heading": "ABSTRACT",
          "page": 10,
          "content": "Herpes zoster (HZ), caused by reactivation of varicella-zoster virus (VZV), increases the risk of cardiovascular and cerebrovascular events. Studies show a sharp rise in ischemic stroke and myocardial infarction within 1–4 weeks after HZ onset—especially in herpes zoster ophthalmicus (HZO)—with risk lasting up to one year. The mechanism involves VZV-related vasculopathy, inflammation, and endothelial injury. In Taiwan, the lifetime risk of HZ is about 32%, and incidence increases in adults ≥50 y…",
